# Production quality by default

Implement features as if they ship to users today: complete wiring, tests, and integration with existing systems.

## Do

- Follow patterns already in `main.ts` bootstraps, `src/character/*`, `src/garments/*`, and `tests/*.spec.ts`
- Add routes to `APP_MODE_LINKS` when adding modes; add headed Playwright tests for new behavior
- Prefer extending shared modules over one-off copies in `main.ts`
- Run build and relevant tests before considering work done

## Do not

- Label work “v1”, “placeholder”, “for now”, or “good enough for demo” when the user asked for the real feature
- Suggest or implement stand-ins for systems that already exist in this repo (especially cloth—see `cloth-physics-required`)
- Leave dead UI, half-wired `window.__*` hooks, or modes that redirect to unrelated pages
- Skip error handling, types, or tests for “speed” on user-facing features

When tradeoffs exist, state them and still default to the **full** production path unless the user explicitly chooses a narrower scope.
